White Chocolate Coconut Cake

1/2 c sugar
1/2 c butter
3 eggs
2 tbsp lemon juice
1/2 tsp vanilla
1 1/2 c flour
1/2 tsp baking soda
1/2 c buttermilk
1/3 c white chocolate chips, melted
1/2 c coconut
2 tsp grated lemon peel

Heat oven to 350F. Grease and flour pan; set aside. In a large bowl, beat sugar and butter on medium speed, until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir in lemon juice and vanilla. Sift together flour and baking soda. Add flour mixture, alternating with buttermilk, mixing well and scraping bowl often. Blend in white chocolate, coconut, and lemon peel. Spoon batter into prepared pan and bake for 22-26 min, until toothpick comes out clean. Cool 10 min in pan; invert onto cooling rack and cool completely. Decorate as desired. 


Notes: Makes 1 cake or 6 cakelets, prob use bundt pan
